<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1527">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/305.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the
                                        Navy</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-20">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 20, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your letter of November 19, enclosing [etc.]</p>
                            <p>It is noted that you suggest that the Admiral in command in Mexican
                                east coast waters be instructed to extend such protection as may be
                                possible to the lives and properties of Americans, British, and.
                                other foreigners at Tampico, as well as to afford them refuge in the
                                event of danger.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor to inform you that the Commander in Chief of the
                                Detached Squadron in Mexican waters has been directed
                                accordingly.</p>
                            <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Josephus Daniels</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>